! scribe

Bidirectional sync between a tiddler field (or sub-path inside a JSON-encoded field) and a state tiddler. Wraps input widgets so they can edit nested values inside a JSON field as if they were plain DataTiddler indexes.

!! Key features

* ''Bidirectional sync'' — state-tiddler ↔ target field, re-prepared on external changes
* ''Sub-path support'' — sync a value at <code>path="0,caption"</code> inside the JSON-encoded field, not just whole fields
* ''Pluggable type handlers'' via <code>module-type: scribetype</code> modules
* ''Three handlers ship'' — <code>text/plain</code>, <code>application/json</code>, <code>application/x-string-array</code>
* ''Empty-state = delete'' — clearing the state removes the sub-path key, useful for "un-set this property" semantics
* ''Zero plugin dependencies''

!! Prerequisites

No external prerequisites. Optional: <code>$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template</code> for the branded documentation hub.

!! Quick start

```
<$scribe tiddler="Task1" field="kind.fields" path="0,caption" type="text/plain">
  <$edit-text tiddler=<<state>> field="text" tag="input"/>
</$scribe>
```

!! Attribution

The bidirectional sync pattern was inspired by Flibbles' <code>FieldTranscriberWidget</code> in [ext[tw5-graph|https://github.com/flibbles/tw5-graph]]. This is an independent reimplementation with sub-path support added.
